The paper deals with a metric on $\mathbb{F}_q^n$ and develops a coding theory for this metric. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the computation of the size of balls with respect to this metric, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper is motivated by the desire to design new code-based cryptographic systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
